betterquesting:10.desc:8:
The orbital station is a very heavy load for a rocket. If you want to launch it from Earth, you will need a multi-stage rocket with a huge amount of fuel and the most powerful engines. (Which is very inefficient) Launching the station from the Moon (Muna) is much easier and cheaper.

On Earth or the Moon, use a radio telescope to program an empty disk for the orbital station - place it in the telescope slot and press the ORB button. At the signal processing station, make a copy of the disk.

Assemble a rocket with the station on board.

Launch the rocket from the launch pad with the disk. A few seconds after launch, the station will deploy in orbit around the Moon.

That's it! Assemble another rocket to the station (you will need a copy of the disk to the station) and fly. The station code on all disks must match, otherwise you won't be able to get to it! (I warned you!)
